      "solution": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.io.*;\nimport java.math.*;\n\nclass Solution {\n\n    public static void main(String args[]) {\n        Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);\n        int nb = in.nextInt();\n        if (in.hasNextLine()) {\n            in.nextLine();\n        }\n        String s1 = in.nextLine();\n        String s2 = in.nextLine();\n        \n        if(nb%2 == 0){\n            nb++;\n            for(int i = 0 ; i < (nb+1)/2; i++){\n                System.out.print(rep(s2,i));\n                System.out.print(rep(s1, nb-2*i));\n                System.out.println(rep(s2,i));\n            }\n        } else {\n             for(int i = (nb-1)/2 ; i >= 0; i--){\n                System.out.print(rep(s2,i));\n                System.out.print(rep(s1, nb-2*i));\n                System.out.println(rep(s2,i));\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    static String rep(String s, int f){\n        String se = \"\";\n        for(int i = 0; i < f ;i++) se +=s;\n        return se;\n    }\n}",
      "statement": "- If the [[nb]] is odd, you write a pyramid.\n- If the [[nb]] is even, you add one to the number and you write a invert pyramid.\n- You fill the pyramid with the symbol on the second line ([[s1]]).\n- The space where you don't write the symbol must be filled by the symbol on the third line ([[s2]].",
